r2407 | andlov | 2016-06-01 01:39:04 +0200 (Wed, 01 Jun 2016) | 1 line

The disk performance collector is now supporting sampling multiple disks at once using an array filter. If unset, then all disks are sampled. Each disk is stored as a separate performance counter event.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r2406 | andlov | 2016-06-01 01:36:25 +0200 (Wed, 01 Jun 2016) | 1 line

The collector base class will set non-blocking mode on opening its process.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r2405 | andlov | 2016-06-01 01:34:44 +0200 (Wed, 01 Jun 2016) | 1 line

Permit non-blocking I/O on process runner. Calling read() in non-blocking mode will return false instead of blocking when pipe is empty. An process in blocking mode can find out number of bytes readable in output buffer (from command) by calling available().
------------------------------------------------------------------------
